<p><strong>Week 6 review:</strong> Rep-triggered suppression rules documented. `high-touch` flag on strategic accounts. Confirm collision calendar updated for upcoming peak weeks and that subscription, wholesale, or gift-buyer tags still suppress conflicting promos.</p>
<p><strong>Stack economics note:</strong> B2B stacks run $200–500/mo — ActiveCampaign ($30–150) + Sequenzy ($50–150) + Klaviyo/Brevo ($50–200). One preserved trade relationship from collision fix can exceed annual stack cost. Model operator hours alongside SaaS fees — governance debt shows up as discount margin leakage before it shows up as tool cost.</p>
